Rodriguez Camp first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Rodriguez Camp had a population of 133. The population density was {{convert|505.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Rodriguez Camp was 14 (10.5%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (0.8%) [[African Americans|African American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 4 (3.0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 85 (63.9%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 29 (21.8%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 127 persons (95.5%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Rodriguez Camp CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0662496 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 1, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 28 households, out of which 16 (57.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 18 (64.3%) were married-couple households, 2 (7.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 2 (7.1%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 6 (21.4%) had a male householder with no partner present. 2 households (7.1%) were one person, and 0 (0.0%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 4.75.<ref name=DP1/> There were 25 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (89.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Rodriguez Camp CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0662496 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 1, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 56 people (42.1%) under the age of 18, 14 people (10.5%) aged 18 to 24, 34 people (25.6%) aged 25 to 44, 16 people (12.0%) aged 45 to 64, and 13 people (9.8%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 23.6{{nbsp}}years. There were 64 males and 69 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 33 housing units at an average density of {{convert|125.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 28 (84.8%) were occupied. Of these, 0 (0.0%) were owner-occupied, and 28 (100.0%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

